<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/5936991-john-paul-feehily"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1316343199i/5936991._UX100_CR0,16,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/5936991-john-paul-feehily">John Paul Feehily</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    This is a subject of some discussion alright. The alliance was always a tentative one. The decision to split was tactically agreed by Brood and Dujek,<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    This is a subject of some discussion alright. The alliance was always a tentative one. The decision to split was tactically agreed by Brood and Dujek, to check both cities. The intention being to meet at Coral together. The Malazans however moved quicker than expected, the question that often comes up is, why did Dujek race ahead. <br />Was it simply to take Coral for the Empire? Ships were already on route. Or another theory is that Dujek and Whiskeyjack knew of Quick Ben and Paran's plans for the Seer. And rushed ahead to support the covert group. No one outside the Malazans was to know (especially Kallor) what they planned for the Seer. Brood was aiming to destroy him outright which probably wouldn't bother the Crippled God too much.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
