<div id="review_708335531" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/708335531" />
    <a title="Terry" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22765690-terry"><img alt="Terry" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1381198765p2/22765690.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/708335531?book_show_action=true">Aug 31, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Terry" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Terry" href="/user/show/22765690-terry">Terry</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780765310033" href="/book/show/618225.Memories_of_Ice">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22765690-terry?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22765690-terry?shelf=2021-book-challenge">2021-book-challenge</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer708335531" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1238127060176725821">So many different story lines, and they&apos;re all good. Some of the best heroic fantasy I&apos;ve read.<br/><br/>***********<br/>After finishing my third read of this book, I still do not have the words to describe my enjoyment. This is one of, if not the, best books I&apos;ve ever read. The second half is so engrossing, and there are so many threads that all tie together, that it is just a true pleasure to take in and enjoy. My emotions at the end were just so piqued...I just sit there dumfounded as I closed the last page</span>
  <span id="freeText1238127060176725821" style="display:none">So many different story lines, and they're all good. Some of the best heroic fantasy I've read.<br /><br />***********<br />After finishing my third read of this book, I still do not have the words to describe my enjoyment. This is one of, if not the, best books I've ever read. The second half is so engrossing, and there are so many threads that all tie together, that it is just a true pleasure to take in and enjoy. My emotions at the end were just so piqued...I just sit there dumfounded as I closed the last page. So many levels of enjoyment. Please pick up this series if you've ever given it a consideration, and at least read through this book. This is where it starts to get laid bare. Very glad to be continuing this series.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1238127060176725821" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


